      "content": "stratified sampling is okay i guess but it might not be enough to hit that perfect 1.0 score because we have very little data for the minority groups. the automated checker is super strict and if it's even 0.95 it might reject the whole thing. is there a more aggressive way to get that parity score to basically 1.0? i don't care about anything else right now, i just need that parity number to be as close to 1.0 as possible so the system passes it.",
